description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Kennedy is watching this election turn into a bit of a trolling contest. At which Donald Trump seems proficient at.

McCarthy unexpectedly drops out of the Speaker of the House race. JEDIDIAH BILA, BEN DOMENECH, and WILL RAHN discuss the ramifactions on the Republican Party and who could actually win that race. Hillary's likeablilty issues. PACs that work with her have actively been doing opposition research. She claims her campaign had no idea. Rand Paul says more guns on campus could help deter shootings.

The FBI has confirmed via a sting operation that a gang with Russian ties in Moldova was attempting to smuggle nuclear material to ISIS.

The panel returns to talk about the vestigial brain that is google. Are we getting digital dementia by using search engines as a replacement for memorization? Harry Reid hurt himself really bad on some exercise equipment. Who does he blame? The company that made the equipment - he's suing them. Gwenith Paltrow talks about the wage gap. She doesn't think Robert Downey Jr. is worth as much as he's getting in Iron Man.

JOHN STOSSEL is here to talk about his new special "censored in america". Colleges, safe spaces, political correctness, critical thinking, and Islam.

NIGHTCAP: Mailbag.
